headlines.description: — RJ Barrett scored 31 points, Scottie Barnes added 17 points in his return from injury, and the Toronto Raptors won back-to-back games for the first time this season by beating the Minnesota Timberwolves 110-105 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Barrett scores 31, Barnes adds 17 in return from injury, and Raptors beat Timberwolves 110-105

events.name: Utah Jazz at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Harrison Barnes had 25 points and 10 rebounds, rookie Stephon Castle scored 18 points and the San Antonio Spurs rallied to defeat the Utah Jazz 126-118 on Thursday night for their second straight win without Victor Wembanyama.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs rally to top Jazz 126-118 for 2nd straight victory without injured Wembanyama

events.name: Orlando Magic at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner hit a go-ahead 3-pointer with 2.5 seconds to play, and the Orlando Magic roared back to snap the Los Angeles Lakers' six-game winning streak with a 119-118 victory Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Franz Wagner hits a clutch 3, and the Magic exploit Davis' mistakes for a 119-118 win over Lakers
